The easiest way to get started with your own Chef server is to launch a fully-functional Amazon Machine Images (AMI) for the Chef server from the AWS Marketplace or from the Microsoft Azure Marketplace.

Both the AMI and Azure Marketplace image are preconfigured with Chef server, the [Chef management console](https://docs.chef.io/manage.html), [Chef reporting](https://docs.chef.io/install_reporting.html), and [Chef Analytics](https://docs.chef.io/analytics.html). Choosing one of these options will more quickly prepare you for our [Get started with Chef Analytics](/get-started-with-chef-analytics/linux/) tutorial, which shows you how to use Chef Analytics to gain insight into what is happening on your Chef server.

You can also install Chef server manually on your own hardware or on another cloud provider.

