## Option 1: Launch Chef server from the AWS Marketplace

The Chef documentation explains how to launch the Chef server from the AMI.

<a class='accent-button radius' href='https://docs.chef.io/aws_marketplace.html' target='_blank'>Install Chef server from the AWS Marketplace&nbsp;&nbsp;<i class='fa fa-external-link'></i></a>

If you followed the other Learn Chef tutorials, you can copy your <% fp 'chef-repo' %> directory that contains the Starter Kit to the <% fp '~/learn-chef' %> directory. Doing so helps keeps your Chef learning materials in one place.

If you are using AMI version 2016-01-20, run these commands from your Chef server to complete the installation process after you run `sudo chef-marketplace-ctl setup`. We'll fix this issue in a later release.

```bash
$ sudo rm -r /var/log/opscode
$ sudo rm -r /var/log/opscode-analytics
$ sudo chef-marketplace-ctl upgrade -s
$ sudo chef-marketplace-ctl upgrade -a
$ sudo opscode-analytics-ctl restart
```

You can then [proceed to the next part](/install-and-manage-your-own-chef-server/linux/manage-a-node-on-your-chef-server), where you'll set up a node to manage, bootstrap it, and apply a basic cookbook.

[END_BOX]

